      • val

        public static double val​(pyobj s)
        The main use here is extracting the double value from a Scalar object returned from indexing a tensor. Double k = val(tensor.get(...)); //works just fine Double k = tensor.get(...).data; //fails because indexing can return tensors too, and data can also be a quantity[]

      • data

        public static quantity[] data​(pyobj s)
        Works just like val() but is the counterpart for tensor objects. Used to retrieve the data in a tensor object without the compiler knowing that it's explicitly a tensor object
